(1) The net profit of the Bank for each financial year shall be determined by the Bank after— (a) allowing for the expences of operations for that year; (b) making provision; (i) for bad and doubtful debts, depreciation of assets and contingencies; (ii) for pensions, gratuities and other benefits for its officers and employees; and (iii) for such other items which are consistent with the Bank 's mandate.
