(2) A person shall not, without the prior approval of the Bank — (a) make, design, engrave, print or reproduce; or (b) use, issue or publish; any article or thing resembling a bank note or coin or so nearly resembling or having such a likeness to a bank note or coin so as to likely be confused with, or mistaken for, such bank note or coin.
