Except as otherwise expressly authorised by this Act, the Bank shall not—
(a) engage in trade, purchase stocks or shares of, or otherwise have a direct interest in any commercial, agricultural, industrial, financial or like undertaking, save as the Bank may acquire as security for, or in satisfaction of, debts due to it, and any interest so acquired shall be disposed of at the earliest convenient opportunity;
